gins to overfit.\n\n6. **TE Spectrum Handling**: You mentioned using Huber loss for $D_\\ell^{TE}$. Since $D_\\ell^{TE}$ can be negative, ensure that the standardization (Step 2) is applied correctly to the linear values. If the distribution of $D_\\ell^{TE}$ is highly skewed, consider using an `asinh` transform instead of keeping it strictly linear, as this provides a smoother transition around zero and better handles the dynamic range than raw linear values.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='7c7815b2-5fd9-4c72-a2cb-92631cfa04b0'



